## 🧠 Phase 0 – Chill Mindset, Simple Tracking & Setup (First 30–60 Days)

### 1. Mindset – Keep It Real & Sustainable
- You are **early**, not behind — enjoy the advantage
- Don’t compare with third-year toppers — compare with your last month
- Quality + small daily wins > 10-hour binge sessions
- College exams & internals matter — don’t sacrifice CGPA below 7.5
- Build **visible proof** early: live projects + applications = recruiters notice you sooner
- Rest is important — burnout in first year is common and kills momentum

### 2. Simple & Easy Tracking (No Overkill)
Use **one Google Sheet** or **Notion page** with these sections:

| Section Name              | What to Track (simple columns)                                              | Why It Helps                     |
|---------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| DSA Progress              | Date • Problems Solved • Difficulty • Platform • Quick Note / Weak Topic   | See consistent growth            |
| Project Tracker           | Project Name • Status • Live Link • GitHub Link • Features Done            | Track building & deployment      |
| Internship Applications   | Date • Company/Platform • Role • Status • Response                         | Know how many you sent           |
| Core Subjects Revision    | Subject • Topic • Date Revised • Confidence (1–10)                         | Stay ready for college + interviews |
| Weekly Reflection         | Week # • Hours Coded • One Win • One Struggle • Energy Level               | Stay motivated & balanced        |

**Sunday 30–45 min check-in** (not 2 hours):
- See what you did this week
- Re-solve 4–6 medium problems you struggled with
- Update trackers
- Plan next 7 days (e.g., “finish blog project + 10 medium problems”)

### 3. Make Online Presence Attractive (Low Effort, High Impact)
**LinkedIn**
- Headline: `B.Tech CSE '29 | 500+ DSA | Full-Stack Learning MERN | Looking for SDE Internships 2027`
- About (4–6 lines): “First-year CSE student passionate about coding & building apps. Solved 400+ DSA problems, deployed 7+ projects. Learning full-stack & open to internships early.”
- Skills: DSA, JavaScript, React.js, Node.js, Git, SQL, C++/Java
- Post 1–2 times/week: project screenshot, problem solved, small progress

**GitHub**
- Bio: `First-Year CSE • Learning Full-Stack • 500+ DSA • Building Projects`
- Pin 5–8 best repos
- Every repo: simple README (what it does, tech used, live link, screenshots)

### 4. Realistic Daily Routines (College-Friendly)
**Normal College Days (1.5–3 hrs/day)**
- 40–60 min → DSA (1–2 medium + 1 revision)
- 40–60 min → Project work / learning (React / Node)
- 20–30 min → Core subject reading / SQL
- 10–15 min → Application or LinkedIn post

**Free Days / Weekends (4–5 hrs/day)**
- 1.5 hrs → DSA (3–4 medium / 1–2 hard)
- 1.5 hrs → Project building / deployment
- 45 min → Core subjects / advanced SQL
- 30 min → Applications / networking

**No zero days rule** — even 30–45 min counts (watch one video + solve one problem)

### 5. Health & Balance – Don’t Ignore This
- Sleep 7+ hrs (college + self-study needs energy)
- Walk / play / gym 20–40 min daily
- One lighter day per week (revision + chill)
- Eat normal food — brain works better with fuel
- Talk to friends/family — don’t isolate in code

## 🛠️ Phase 1 – DSA Depth + Core Subjects + Full-Stack Push  
**(Months 1–12 – Your Second Year Timeline)**

### 1. DSA – Build Strong Medium Base (Quality Over Crazy Numbers)
**Focus:** Medium problems (70%) + some hard (20%) + easy revision (10%)

**Easy Monthly Plan (Not Overwhelming)**
**Months 1–3**
- Advanced Arrays: Kadane, sliding window (variable), 2 pointers (3Sum, container water)
- Strings: longest substring without repeat, group anagrams
- Binary Search: rotated array, kth smallest variants

**Months 4–6**
- Linked List: reverse groups, cycle detection, LRU cache intro
- Stack/Queue: next greater element, trapping rain water
- Recursion & Backtracking: subsets II, permutations II, N-Queens basics

**Months 7–9**
- Trees: level order zigzag, max path sum intro, LCA basics
- BST: validate, kth smallest
- Heaps: kth largest, merge k sorted lists intro

**Months 10–12**
- Graphs basics: BFS/DFS grid, number of islands
- Greedy: jump game, activity selection
- Company-tagged medium (Amazon, Microsoft, Flipkart)

**Realistic Targets by End Second Year**
- Total: 600–900 (comfortable range)
- Medium: 400–600
- Hard: 100–200 (only if you enjoy them)
- LeetCode: 200–350+ mediums solved

**Resources (Pick 2–3)**
- Striver SDE Sheet (best for medium focus)
- Love Babbar 450
- takeUforward YouTube
- GeeksforGeeks practice
- NeetCode 150 / Blind 75

**Rule:** Struggle 20–30 min → hint → try again → solution. Write clean code + note time/space.

### 2. Core Subjects – Strong Enough for Interviews
**OOP**
- SOLID basics + examples
- Inheritance vs Composition
- Singleton & Factory pattern intro

**DBMS & SQL**
- Joins (self, outer), group by, having
- Window functions intro (RANK, ROW_NUMBER)
- Normalization (1NF–3NF)
- Practice: LeetCode SQL easy-medium

**OS**
- Process vs thread
- Deadlock conditions + prevention
- Paging & virtual memory basics

**CN**
- TCP 3-way handshake
- HTTP vs HTTPS
- OSI layers simple

**Resources**
- Gate Smashers YouTube (Hindi/English)
- GeeksforGeeks quick articles
- Jenny's Lectures (if you like detailed)

### 3. Full-Stack Push (MERN – Most Jobs in 2026–2027)
**Frontend (Months 1–5)**
- HTML/CSS: responsive, flex/grid, dark mode
- JavaScript: async/await, fetch, modules
- React: useState/useEffect, router, context API
- Tailwind CSS (learn it — super fast in 2026)

**Backend (Months 5–10)**
- Node + Express: routes, middleware
- MongoDB: CRUD, basic queries
- Auth: JWT + bcrypt basics
- Deployment: Vercel (frontend) + Render/Railway (backend)

**Projects – Build These (Deploy All)**
1. Advanced To-Do / Task App (auth, drag-drop, categories, dark mode)
2. Personal Blog (posts CRUD, rich editor, comments)
3. Mini E-commerce (products, cart, filters)
4. Basic Real-Time Chat (Socket.io intro)
5. Expense Tracker (charts with Chart.js, export)
6. Portfolio with Admin Panel (dynamic projects)

**Tip:** After each project → post on LinkedIn: “Just deployed my blog app! Live link below.”

